content:
When you dig more deeply into Omni-Channel and the routing process, there are two particular objects that are worth understanding better: PendingServiceRouting (PSR) and AgentWork.

Available in: both Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience
Omni-Channel is available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

What Is PSR? What Is AgentWork?

PSR (PendingServiceRouting) is a Salesforce object that gets created when work is routed using Omni-Channel. It's a transient object that contains routing information about a work item that is in the midst of being routed.

AgentWork is a Salesforce object that automatically gets created when the routing system finds a potential agent to handle the work item. It contains information about the work item and the routing status.

Why Should I Care?

When a record’s owner is assigned to an Omni-Enabled Queue, or the record is routed via the Omni-Flow Route Work action, a PSR record is created automatically.

What Is the Basic Lifecycle?

A PSR record is created when a work item is routed using Omni-Channel. When the system finds a potential agent to handle the work item, an AgentWork record is created. When an agent accepts the work item, the system deletes the PSR record.

The system never automatically deletes the AgentWork record, but the record can be deleted manually when it enters a non-active state.

What Is the Detailed PSR and AgentWork Lifecycle?

To fully understand the lifecycle of these two objects, refer to this state diagram. The PSR record is transient whereas the AgentWork record sticks around until it's explicitly deleted.

Why does AgentWork contain multiple work records for the same work?

Each time a work item is assigned to an agent, a record is created in AgentWork. If the work item is routed to the same agent multiple times, AgentWork can have multiple active records for the work item.

When is the AgentWork record set to Closed?

An AgentWork record isn’t closed until one of these events happens:

For tab-based capacity, a record closes when the assigned agent closes the work tab.
For status-based capacity, the record closes when the work has a completed status or the work is reassigned.
If After Conversation Work is enabled, the work closes if the After Conversation Work period ends.

You can view the number of Pending Service Routing records that are currently in use in your org, as well as the current hourly use rate. From Setup, enter Omni-Channel in the Quick Find box and select Limits.
title: Understanding Omni-Channel Routing Lifecycle
